      {
        "label": "Introduction: California Dreamin’",
        "href": "xhtml/Flyv_9780593239520_epub3_itr_r1.xhtml",
        "subitems": []
      },
      {
        "label": "Chapter 1: Think Slow, Act Fast: The record of big projects is even worse than it seems.",
        "href": "xhtml/Flyv_9780593239520_epub3_c001_r1.xhtml",
        "subitems": []
      },
      {
        "label": "Chapter 2: The Commitment Fallacy: You need to commit, but not in the way you think.",
        "href": "xhtml/Flyv_9780593239520_epub3_c002_r1.xhtml",
        "subitems": []
      },
      {
        "label": "Chapter 3: Think from Right to Left: Start with the most basic question of all: Why?",
        "href": "xhtml/Flyv_9780593239520_epub3_c003_r1.xhtml",
        "subitems": []
      },
      {
        "label": "Chapter 4: Pixar Planning: Plan like Pixar and Frank Gehry do.",
        "href": "xhtml/Flyv_9780593239520_epub3_c004_r1.xhtml",
        "subitems": []
      },
      {
        "label": "Chapter 5: Are You Experienced?: Experience is often misunderstood and marginalized.",
        "href": "xhtml/Flyv_9780593239520_epub3_c005_r1.xhtml",
        "subitems": []
      },
      {
        "label": "Chapter 6: So You Think Your Project Is Unique?: Think again. Your project is “one of those.”",
        "href": "xhtml/Flyv_9780593239520_epub3_c006_r1.xhtml",
        "subitems": []
      },
      {
        "label": "Chapter 7: Can Ignorance Be Your Friend?: Planning ruins projects, some say. But is it true?",
        "href": "xhtml/Flyv_9780593239520_epub3_c007_r1.xhtml",
        "subitems": []
      },
      {
        "label": "Chapter 8: A Single, Determined Organism: Everyone must row in the same direction: toward delivery.",
        "href": "xhtml/Flyv_9780593239520_epub3_c008_r1.xhtml",
        "subitems": []
      },
      {
        "label": "Chapter 9: What’s Your Lego?: Modularity is the key to building at world-transforming scale.",
        "href": "xhtml/Flyv_9780593239520_epub3_c009_r1.xhtml",
        "subitems": []
      },
